## ⚙️ Configuration

KeyShield stores configuration in `~/.keyshield/config.json`.

### Scan Profiles

| Profile | Description | Detectors | Clipboard Monitor |
|---------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|
| `quick` | Fast essential scan | 10 (skips Memory, ScreenCapture) | Disabled |
| `standard` | Balanced full scan | All 12 | 1.5s |
| `paranoid` | Maximum sensitivity | All 12 + lower thresholds | 3.0s |

### Whitelist

Reduce false positives by whitelisting trusted processes:

```python
from keyshield.core.config import get_config

config = get_config()
config.add_to_whitelist("my_custom_monitoring_tool")
config.remove_from_whitelist("some_process")
```

Or edit `~/.keyshield/config.json` directly:

```json
{
  "whitelist": [
    "my_custom_monitoring_tool",
    "another_trusted_process"
  ]
}
```

### Built-in Whitelist

KeyShield ships with a whitelist of ~60 common legitimate processes including:
- System processes (`systemd`, `init`, `svchost.exe`, etc.)
- Desktop environments (GNOME, KDE, XFCE, etc.)
- Common applications (browsers, editors, terminals)
- Development tools

