## 🏗️ Architecture

```
keyshield/
├── core/
│   ├── engine.py          # Scan orchestration, dedup, profiles
│   ├── config.py          # Configuration, whitelist, self-exclusion
│   └── threat_db.py       # Signatures, keywords, IoCs
├── detectors/
│   ├── base_detector.py   # Shared base class with self-exclusion
│   ├── keylogger_detector.py
│   ├── hook_detector.py   # Cross-platform (Windows + Linux)
│   ├── process_detector.py
│   ├── clipboard_monitor.py
│   ├── screen_capture_detector.py
│   ├── network_exfil_detector.py
│   ├── dll_injection_detector.py  # DLL (Win) + .so (Linux)
│   ├── persistence_detector.py
│   ├── memory_scanner.py
│   ├── kernel_module_detector.py  # Linux rootkit detection
│   ├── usb_detector.py           # BadUSB / Rubber Ducky
│   └── scheduled_task_detector.py # Task Scheduler / cron
├── utils/
│   ├── logger.py          # Rotating log files
│   ├── reporter.py        # JSON, TXT, CSV export
│   ├── system_info.py     # Cross-platform system info
│   └── helpers.py         # Hashing, admin check, path safety
├── cli/
│   └── main.py            # Argparse CLI with --web flag
└── web/
    ├── app.py             # Flask app with SSE, thread-safe state
    ├── templates/         # Jinja2 HTML templates
    └── static/            # CSS, JS, images
```

### Key Design Decisions

1. **BaseDetector Pattern** — All detectors inherit from `BaseDetector`, which provides `self.safe_process_iter()` (skips own PIDs + whitelist) and config access.

2. **Self-Exclusion** — `Config._collect_own_pids()` tracks KeyShield's PID tree so detectors never flag themselves. This eliminates the most common false positive.

3. **Tiered Keyword Matching** — `SUSPICIOUS_PROCESS_KEYWORDS` (strong, 1 match = flag) vs `WEAK_SUSPICIOUS_KEYWORDS` (need 2+ matches). Dramatically reduces false positives on generic words like "monitor".

4. **Finding Deduplication** — Engine deduplicates by `(pid, title)` tuple before returning results.

5. **Thread-Safe Web State** — `threading.Lock` protects `_scan_state` and `_scan_history` from race conditions.

